<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,960,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,960,986]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Third antennomer smaller than the second (I&lt;III&lt;II&lt;IV&lt;V). Anterolateral margin of pronotum not punctured (
<figureCitation box="[279,381,997,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Posterior part of pronotum with black punctures (
<figureCitation box="[958,1060,997,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with black punctures anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[275,376,1033,1059]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process with arms of anterior bifurcation robust and receiving 1/2 of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[258,359,1069,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). Connexivum flat (
<figureCitation box="[577,676,1069,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Pseudosutures without adjacent dark green spot (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1331,1069,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[269,337,1104,1131]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,890,914]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,197,851]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1435,181,866]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Female genital plates: A—ventral view, B—oblique view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911516/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Valvifers VIII with distal margin sloping (red arrow) and slightly arched; outer angle acuminated and carinated, this carina also swollen along mediolateral crest (black arrow); mesial borders shallowly excavated. Valvulae IX not exposed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[441,612,1176,1203]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,886,1212,1239]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,960,1347]" box="[199,886,1212,1239]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1212,1238]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,444,1213,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1988,2012]" captionTargetBox="[162,1430,319,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-81@17.[151,1435,307,1971]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distributional map of the species H. triangularis group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911540/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[464,618,1213,1239]" name="Colombia" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
