<collectingRegion box="[768,882,1213,1239]" country="Colombia" name="Santander" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Santander</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,960,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1248,1274]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is the only one in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[722,899,1248,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,899,1248,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group that has black punctures on pronotum. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,364,1285,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,364,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Hypoxys ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[370,433,1285,1311]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[370,433,1285,1311]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[485,614,1285,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[485,614,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">H. curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[621,683,1285,1311]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[621,683,1285,1311]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share the distal margin of each valvifer VIII with a distal spine. The 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,295,1321,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,295,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">H. ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[303,366,1321,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[303,366,1321,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be separated by valvifers VIII carinate (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[893,1023,1321,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[893,1023,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">H. curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1031,1094,1321,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1031,1094,1321,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
valvifers VIII never carinate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
